Minister Nathi Mthethwa has defended the multi-million-rand project, saying it is part of the department's mandate. eNCA reporter, Pule Letshwiti-Jones, has been getting reaction to the flag project. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - You would think we have better things to spend our money on, but apparently not R22-million for a flag pole. The Department of Arts and Culture wants to erect the flag at Freedom Park in Pretoria. READ: Mthethwa defends R22m flag project Minister Nathi Mthethwa has defended the multi-million-rand project, saying it is part of the department's mandate. But South Africans say they've got a million ideas about what they would do with R22-million, and a flag is not one of them. They want government to use the flag project money to tackle a mountain of service delivery issues facing municipalities.